        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 2:40PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 240 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Adena School, or 6 miles south of Fort Morgan, moving northeast at
10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brush.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
